8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Private right of action -- definitions. (1) (a) A minor who attends a
11 performance in violation of 20-7-135 or
12 a minor or adult who attends a performance of a drag queen or drag king may bring an action against a
13 person who knowingly promotes, conducts, or participates as a performer in the performance.
14 (b) A minor's parent or legal guardian may bring an action in the name of the minor for an action
15 commenced under this section.
16 (2) If a person prevails in an action brought under this section, the court shall award:
17 (a) actual damages, including damages for psychological, emotional, economic, and physical
18 harm;
19 (b) reasonable attorney fees and costs incurred in bringing the action; and
20 (c) statutory damages of $5,000.
21 (3) A person may bring an action under this section not later than 2 years from the date the cause
22 of action accrues.
23 (4) As used in this section, the following definitions apply:
24 (a) "Drag king" means a female or male performer who embodies an exaggerated masculine
25 persona with a strong emphasis on sexual energy, eroticism, and provocative performance art. Their acts often
26 include sexually suggestive movements, stripping, fetish-inspired attire, and themes of dominance or seduction.
27 They have been known to historically perform in libraries, schools, adult entertainment venues, burlesque
28 shows, and private events where explicit content is expected. Their performances often challenge gender
